defaultHowever, the government says: ‘We do not accept the view that the proposed residence test would result in contravention of our domestic and international legal obligations ... we would ensure that legal aid will continue to be 
defaultavailable where necessary to comply with our obligations u
defaultnder EU or international law set
default out in Schedule 1 to LASPO.’
default This is based on the supposed availability of except
defaultional funding as a 
defaultsafeguard for those excluded from legal aid by the residence tes
defaultt.
